.SH NAME
\*LXmCreateInformationDialog\*O\(emThe MessageBox InformationDialog convenience creation function
.iX "XmCreateInformationDialog"
.iX "creation functions" "XmCreateInformationDialog"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Xm/MessageB.h>
.sp \n(PDu
Widget XmCreateInformationDialog (\*Vparent, name, arglist, argcount\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Widget	\*Vparent\*L;
	String	\*Vname\*L;
	ArgList	\*Varglist\*L;
	Cardinal	\*Vargcount\*L;
.wH .fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LXmCreateInformationDialog\*O is a convenience creation function that creates
a DialogShell and an unmanaged MessageBox child of the DialogShell.
An InformationDialog gives the user information, such as the status of
an action.
It includes a symbol, a message, and three buttons.
The default symbol is a lower case \*Li\*O.
The default button labels are \*LOK\*O, \*LCancel\*O, and \*LHelp\*O.
.PP 
Use \*LXtManageChild\*O to pop up the InformationDialog (passing the MessageBox
as the widget parameter); use \*LXtUnmanageChild\*O to pop it down.
.VL .75i 
.LI "\*Vparent\*O"
Specifies the parent widget ID
.LI "\*Vname\*O"
Specifies the name of the created widget
.LI "\*Varglist\*O"
Specifies the argument list
.LI "\*Vargcount\*O"
Specifies the number of attribute/value pairs in the argument list
(\*Varglist\*O)
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of MessageBox and its associated resources, see
\*LXmMessageBox(3X)\*O.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the MessageBox widget ID.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.na
\*LXmMessageBox(3X)\*O.
.ad
